Class NetPlayer

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.rmi.server.RemoteObject
      • java.rmi.server.RemoteServer
        • java.rmi.server.UnicastRemoteObject
          • breakthroughPP.players.NetPlayer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Player, Setting, java.io.Serializable, java.rmi.Remote

    public class NetPlayer
extends java.rmi.server.UnicastRemoteObject
implements Player, Setting
    The NetPlayer class works as a wrapper class to be able to store any Player as well as to contain the funcions required for accessing a remote player on another computer in the net. source code origin from: Brosenne, H.: Allgemeines Programmierpraktikum, Sommersemester 2016, Georg-August-Universität Göttingen, S.156. modified by Georg-August University Goettingen APP breakthroughPP SoSe 2016 CodeSalat Jan-Philipp Burchert
